Description: Rest on the Flight into Egypt; Holy Family resting in landscape, with reclining figure of Virgin on the left watching over Child sitting astride her leg, and St Joseph resting his head on his right hand, while the donkey is grazing on the r Etching
Curator's comments: Another impression: 1928,1126.1. Attributed in the Bartsch Commentary volume to Francesco Amato (.008), despite the JB monogram on the plate.
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (Inscribed on the verso with CMC monogram in Cracherode's hand (L.607) and dated 1786)
